text.data-name: The Application and accompanying documents shall be submitted to the IEC at least 8 (eight) weeks prior to the expected date of implementation of the research study in the case of an ordinary review process.
text.tspan: The Application and accompanying documents shall
be submitted to the IEC at least 8 (eight) weeks prior
to the expected date of implementation of the
research study in the case of an ordinary review
process.

text.data-name: The IEC Manager will issue a formal communication to the Applicant regarding the approval or rejection of the Application.
text.tspan: The IEC Manager will issue a formal communication
to the Applicant regarding the approval or rejection
of the Application.

text.data-name: Feedback from the IEC is shared with the Applicant for resolution.
text.tspan: Feedback from the IEC is shared with the Applicant
for resolution.

text.data-name: The IEC Manager will thereafter confirm whether the Application can be processed by the Catalyst Foundation IEC within 5-7 days upon receiving the synopsis of the research study.
text.tspan: The IEC Manager will thereafter confirm
whether the Application can be processed by
the Catalyst Foundation IEC within 5-7 days
upon receiving the synopsis of the research

text.data-name: For expedited review, the application needs to be submitted at least 5 (five) weeks before the expected date of implementation of the study.
text.tspan: For expedited review, the application needs to
be submitted at least 5 (five) weeks before the
expected date of implementation of the study.

text.data-name: Submission of the final report of the study after its completion; and

text.tspan: Consent Forms and Templates (including scripts,

text.data-name: In some cases, the Applicant may be required to make a presentation to the IEC to determine the overall approval of their feedback.
text.tspan: In some cases, the Applicant may be required to make a

text.data-name: The IEC shall then either provide a unanimous decision on approving the research study or reject the Application if the Applicant has not appropriately justified their feedback despite multiple attempts to do so.
text.tspan: The IEC shall then either provide a unanimous decision on
approving the research study or reject the Application if the
Applicant has not appropriately justified their feedback
despite multiple attempts to do so.

text.data-name: Certificate of Completion for the Research Ethics Test
text.tspan: Certificate of Completion for the Research Ethics Test

text.data-name: A preliminary call may be scheduled by the IEC Manager to understand the nature of the study, its objectives, and its subject matter.
text.tspan: A preliminary call may be scheduled by the IEC
Manager to understand the nature of the study,
its objectives, and its subject matter.

text.data-name: This is also to ensure that the Application and accompanying documents submitted are appropriately vetted by the member Secretariat.
text.tspan: This is also to ensure that the Application and
accompanying documents submitted are
appropriately vetted by the member Secretariat.

text.data-name: Regular updates from the Applicant on any proposed changes to the study, whether material or not in nature.
text.tspan: Regular updates from the Applicant on any proposed
changes to the study, whether material or not in nature.

text.data-name: Based on the confirmation shared by the IEC Manager following Step 1, the Application template and a list of the required documents shall be shared with the Applicant.
text.tspan: Based on the confirmation shared by the IEC
Manager following Step 1, the Application template
and a list of the required documents shall be shared
with the Applicant.

text.data-name: The resolutions shared by the Applicant are reviewed by the IEC.
text.tspan: The resolutions shared by the Applicant are reviewed
by the IEC.

text.data-name: The IEC will continue to monitor the research annually for the entire duration of the Project and beyond. Further, the Applicant will share any final deliverables/publications that are developed as a result of the study/research.
text.tspan: The IEC will continue to monitor the research
annually for the entire duration of the Project and
beyond. Further, the Applicant will share any final
deliverables/publications that are developed as a
result of the study/research.

text.data-name: The vetted Application and documents are shared with the IEC for their review.

with the IEC for their review.
